        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quogue%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Quogue Historic District, listed on the National Register, contains more than 250 contributing structures.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://villageofquogueny.gov/historic-district/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In January, village trustees celebrated the tenth anniversary of the district’s National Register listing.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://villageofquogueny.gov/historic-district/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The district’s architecture chronicles Quogue’s shift from an early agricultural community to a seasonal one in the nineteenth century.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://villageofquogueny.gov/historic-district/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Quogue has no passport office; nearby options include the Westhampton Beach Post Office and the Patchogue‑Medford Library.",
